description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Band 7 /Ward Senior Sister on the Neurology and Stroke Rehabilitation Unit at Southmead Hospital. The ward is a key part of the Neurosciences and Musculoskeletal Division, and the 33-bed unit provides outstanding patient care for Neurology and Stroke Rehabilitation patients. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a highly committed Sister (Band 6) for the role of Senior Sister (Band 7) to join and lead the team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a Band 7 you will be expected to lead and work closely with all members of the multidisciplinary team and have an effective communication skills to manage the treatment, care and flow of patients. You will need to be enthusiastic and have a wide range of clinical skills and willingness to engage with all staff.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a senior member of the team you will be leading in developing the nursing team, supporting and teaching both registered and non-registered staff and contributing to the enhancement of evidenced based nursing care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you wish to discuss this opportunity further please contact Matron Emerline Albano via email. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;emerline.albano@nbt.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
